Russia Ex Egypt
- Moscow. 27 Nov 2017. In Moscow (Municipal infection hospital #1, Federal research epidemiology institute) we registered 2 cases of dengue fever without hemorrhagic symptoms after travel to Hurghada. In PCR described DENV-2, and in MAC-ELISA - anti-DENV IgM. Case #1 woman 63-years-old, she was in Hurghada 12-28.10.2017, her disease started 18.10.2017, and fever duration approximately 7 days. After return she admitted in our hospital with temperature 37,5 and mild symptoms. Case #2 man 49-years-old, was in Hurghada 28.10-17.11, his disease started 15.11, and had typical signs: low WBC, thrombocytopenia, fever, weakness, headache.
Contributed by: Muhammad Saifullin, infection physician.email: dr_saifullin@mail.ru

Malaysia
- National .21 Nov 2017. Dengue risk back in Fair Park, with 15 residents contracting the illness. Dr Mah said Kinta remained the district with the highest number of dengue cases with 2997 recorded, with 5 deaths. "This is a 75.5 percent increase from last year [2016], whereby we recorded 1708 cases," he said, adding that other notable districts with an increase in dengue cases included Larut, Matang and Selama (535 cases with 2 deaths), Kuala Kangsar (281 cases and 2 deaths) and Kampar (248 cases and one death)," he added. Other districts included Batang Padang (230 cases), Hulu Perak (157), Perak Tengah (80) and Muallim (81). Dr Mah said districts with lower dengue incidence were Manjung, which saw a 39.6 percent drop of cases from 361 to 218, Hilir Perak (162 to 152) and Kerian (111 to 76).
https://www.thestar.com.my/metro/metro-news/2017/11/21/dengue-risk-back-in-fair-park-neighbourhood-taken-off-hotspot-list-but-cleanliness-not-well-maintain/
